    {
      "content": "How you manage devices",
      "pos": [
        1338,
        1360
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1361,
        1519
      ],
      "content": "Manage devices using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Office 365 admin center<ept id=\"p1\">](https://support.office.com/article/About-the-Office-365-admin-center-58537702-d421-4d02-8141-e128e3703547)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "If you use <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph> by itself, you manage devices using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Intune admin console<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn646966.aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        1520,
        1699
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you integrate Intune with System Center 2012 Configuration Manager, you use the Configuration Manager console to manage devices on-premises and in the cloud.",
      "pos": [
        1711,
        1871
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Devices you can manage",
      "pos": [
        1874,
        1896
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Cloud-based management for iOS, Android, and Windows Phone",
      "pos": [
        1897,
        1955
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Cloud-based management for iOS, Mac OS X, Android, Windows Phone, and Windows PCs",
      "pos": [
        1956,
